<section class="overview">
  <h2>5-Year Master Plan</h2>

  <div class="benefits">
    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>2026 — Hard Backpacking Trip</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Training and preparation</p>
      <p>Late summer/fall training hike to build endurance and skills. Scouts ages 13-15 welcome. Multi-day trip on the Appalachian Trail or similar terrain.</p>
      <p><em>Eligibility: 13+ at time of trip</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>2027 — Northern Tier</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Wilderness canoeing</p>
      <p>Boundary Waters canoe expedition in Minnesota. 6-10 days paddling 50-150 miles.</p>
      <p><em>Eligibility: 14+ at time of trip</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>2028 — Philmont</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Backpacking at altitude</p>
      <p>12-day or 9-day trek through the Sangre de Cristo Mountains. 50-100+ miles with full pack.</p>
      <p><em>Eligibility: 14+ at time of trip</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>2029 — Troop Choice + Multi-Crew</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Options and mentorship</p>
      <p>Troop vote on destination (Sea Base or Summit), plus crews to bases experienced scouts want to revisit.</p>
      <p><em>Eligibility varies by base</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>2030+ — Sea Base & Rotation</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Water-based adventure</p>
      <p>Florida Sea Base scuba/sailing/island adventure. Then the cycle begins again!</p>
      <p><em>Eligibility: 13+ at time of trip</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="overview">
  <h2>Qualification Requirements</h2>

  <h3>General Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete annual health form (parts A, B, C)</li>
    <li>Current BSA membership</li>
    <li>Swim classification (for water-based programs)</li>
    <li>Personal camping/hiking experience</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>By Base</h3>
  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h4>Philmont</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>14 years old OR 8th grade graduate</li>
      <li>Complete Physical Exam (Part C of health form)</li>
      <li>Backpacking experience recommended</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Northern Tier</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>14 years old OR 8th grade graduate</li>
      <li>Strong swimming ability (swim test required)</li>
      <li>Comfortable in wilderness settings</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Sea Base</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>13 years old (by arrival date)</li>
      <li>BSA Swimmer classification</li>
      <li>No prohibited medical conditions</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Summit</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Typically 14+ for high adventure programs</li>
      <li>Moderate fitness required</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

